attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This MIPS32 ELF binary is a malicious DDoS (Distributed Denial of Service) bot, likely a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt malware families. The sample implements multiple network flooding techniques, including SYN, ACK, ICMP, and UDP floods (seen in functions like sub_413694, sub_41416c, and sub_413ac0). It exhibits typical botnet behavior such as process killing to remove competition (scanning /proc/net/tcp and killing processes in _CTOR_1) and SSDP discovery via M-SEARCH HTTP templates. A hardcoded C2 IP address, 94.156.152.6, was identified in sub_417348.
